def count_inversions(arr):
    inv_count = 0

    for i in range(len(arr)):
        for j in range(i + 1, len(arr)):
            if arr[i] > arr[j]:
                inv_count += 1

    return inv_count
```

This function iterates through the list and counts pairs that are out of order, which is an inversion. This brute force approach has a time complexity of O(n^2), where n is the length of the array. For larger arrays or efficiency requirements, a more optimized approach using merge sort could be considered to achieve a time complexity of O(n log n).

